🧠 System Working Principle

Muscle contraction generates small electrical signals (EMG).

Gel electrodes capture the bio-signal from the skin.

The BioAmp EXG Pill amplifies the signal to a readable voltage level.

The ESP32 reads the analog signal using its ADC.

Signal processing or threshold detection determines whether a contraction occurred.

Based on the detected signal, the ESP32 sends commands to move the robotic hand servos.

📊 Signal Processing Approach

Basic processing steps used:

Analog signal acquisition

Noise filtering

Threshold detection

Command generation

Future improvements may include:

Digital filtering

Feature extraction

Machine learning based gesture recognition
